INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (116,2,'2021-04-12 11:35:41','2021-04-12 11:35:41','<i><b>Starboy</b></i> is the third studio album by Canadian singer <a title=\"The Weeknd\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Weeknd\">the Weeknd</a>. It was released on November 25, 2016, through <a title=\"XO (record label)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/XO_(record_label)\">XO</a> and <a title=\"Republic Records\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republic_Records\">Republic Records</a>. The album features <a title=\"Guest appearance\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guest_appearance\">guest appearances</a> from <a title=\"Daft Punk\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daft_Punk\">Daft Punk</a>, <a title=\"Lana Del Rey\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lana_Del_Rey\">Lana Del Rey</a>, <a title=\"Kendrick Lamar\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kendrick_Lamar\">Kendrick Lamar</a>, and <a title=\"Future (rapper)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Future_(rapper)\">Future</a>. It was supported by seven <a title=\"Single (music)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Single_(music)\">singles</a>: \"<a title=\"Starboy (song)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Starboy_(song)\">Starboy</a>\", \"<a title=\"I Feel It Coming\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I_Feel_It_Coming\">I Feel It Coming</a>\", \"<a title=\"Party Monster (song)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Party_Monster_(song)\">Party Monster</a>\", \"<a title=\"Reminder (song)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reminder_(song)\">Reminder</a>\", \"<a title=\"Rockin\' (song)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rockin%27_(song)\">Rockin\'</a>\", \"<a title=\"Die for You (song)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Die_for_You_(song)\">Die for You</a>\", and \"<a title=\"Secrets (The Weeknd song)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Secrets_(The_Weeknd_song)\">Secrets</a>\".\r\n\r\n<i>Starboy</i> received generally favorable reviews from critics and debuted at number one on the US <a title=\"Billboard 200\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Billboard_200\"><i>Billboard</i> 200</a>, with 348,000 <a title=\"Album-equivalent unit\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Album-equivalent_unit\">album-equivalent units</a>, 209,000 of which were pure sales. It also debuted at number one on <i><a title=\"Billboard (magazine)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Billboard_(magazine)\">Billboard</a></i><span class=\"nowrap\">\'</span>s <a title=\"Canadian Albums Chart\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canadian_Albums_Chart\">Canadian Albums Chart</a>. In January 2019, the album was certified <a title=\"RIAA certification\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RIAA_certification\">triple platinum</a> by the <a title=\"Recording Industry Association of America\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recording_Industry_Association_of_America\">Recording Industry Association of America</a> (RIAA). The album won <a title=\"Grammy Award for Best Progressive R&amp;B Album\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grammy_Award_for_Best_Progressive_R%26B_Album\">Best Urban Contemporary Album</a> at the <a title=\"60th Annual Grammy Awards\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/60th_Annual_Grammy_Awards\">2018 Grammy Awards</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSource: <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Starboy_(album)\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Starboy_(album)</a>','Starboy','Starboy is the third studio album by Canadian singer The Weeknd.','publish','closed','closed','','starboy','','','2021-04-13 02:55:07','2021-04-13 02:55:07','',0,'http://noted.local/?post_type=album&#038;p=116',0,'album','',0);
